{"key":"processedPost-9401521","value":{"id":9401521,"first":9401443,"last":9401589,"when":1228870389,"utime":"12/10/08 02:53 AM","cleanedPost":"Squeeze it until the excess is drained out before you spawn.&nbsp; If it's too wet, colonization is slowed, and that can allow contaminants to get a foothold.&nbsp; <br />What you're looking for is when you hold a handful of substrate, it doesn't drip at all.&nbsp; If you squeeze gently, you might get a drop or two that drips out, and if you squeeze hard, you'll get a small stream for a couple of seconds, but then it stops.&nbsp; The above is what we call 'field capacity' and is what you're looking for.<br />RR"}}